<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-02-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="493" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d493">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/962.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-24">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 24, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I am requested to inform you that the Dominican Government has
                            definitively accepted the proposal of the National City Bank, after
                            seriously considering all the objections raised by the National Bank of
                            Santo Domingo. Your instructions have been strictly complied with and I
                            have declared on all occasions that my Government leaves the Dominican
                            Government absolutely free to choose between the two propositions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>